    {
      "type": "button",
      "name": "button",
      "value": "Evaluate task group completion",
      "action_list": "click | task: evaluate | data_list_name: @local.data_list_b, row_id: @local.row_id_b;\nclick | task: evaluate | data_list_name: @local.data_list_a;",
      "comments": "This example uses local variables to more closely resemble a real-world use case. But values can also be provided directly to the action paramaters.\n\nThe order of actions is important when calling the action multiple times together: the lowest-level task should be evaluated first to ensure that any changes are reflected higher up.\n\nThe second action invocation demonstrates that the \"row_id\" parameter is optional: if not provided then every task row of the source data list will be evaluated."
    },
    {
      "type": "title",
      "value": "debug_task_group_a"
    },
